      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i think something is wrong with my smart home setup. i noticed that whenever i'm feeling really stressed or upset, my thermostat cranks the heat up way higher than i set it, and my smart fridge started making this weird humming sound right after i had a bad argument on the phone earlier. it feels like they're reacting to what's happening in the room. is there some kind of sensor or software link that would let them track my mood like that?",
